<br>
Ayslyn sat back and grinned.  “Let me tell you all about Rose,” he said with a laugh.<br>
<br>
***** <br>
<br>
The three companions rode north and east through the plains.  Ayslyn sat forlornly on his destrier.  Alec looked at him contemptuously for a moment before stating, “Oh stop sulking.”<br>
<br>
Ayslyn sighed and looked at his friend.   “Why the Tomb of Swords though?  Couldn’t you have found a Tomb of Bows?”<br>
<br>
Alec rolled his eyes and continued to ignore his friend.  Terrellion looked back and forth between them.  “Cheer up Ays.  This’ll be fun.”<br>
<br>
Ayslyn glared at him for a moment before returning to his sulk.  After a few minutes he spoke up.  “It’s just that we find every other magical weapon in creation except bows.  Magic swords, magic sticks,”<br>
<br>
Alec looked at him dangerously, “Miranda’s friend explained that to you.  That was a Staff of the magi.  And you almost snapped it in half you nit.”<br>
<br>
“How was I supposed to know?  It looked like a stick to me.  Anyway, we even found a damned magical scythe.  But, the only magical bow around here is the one I had made.”<br>
<br>
Alec looked at him for a few moments before replying, “Maybe if you’re lucky, one of the adventurers in there was an archer.”<br>
<br>
Ayslyn brightened up immediately.  “Ya think so?”<br>
<br>
Alec looked at him, surprised.  “Um….   Sure,” he shrugged.<br>
<br>
Ayslyn grinned happily and nudged his horse into a quick run.  Alec shook his head in wonderment.  “That boy is strange.” He grinned<br>
