<br>
Terrellion crumpled the scroll in his fist and swore.  Ayslyn looked up from his fletching curiously.  “What’s the matter Terr?”<br>
<br>
“It’s a letter from my family back on Evermeet.  There is trouble.”<br>
<br>
Alec sat in one of the chairs by the window, a glass of wine in one hand.  “What kind of trouble?”<br>
<br>
“Someone is out to steal our Moonblade.”<br>
<br>
Alec let out a long, low whistle, impressed.  “Your family has a Moonblade?  That would make you…”<br>
<br>
Terrellion nodded.  “That’s right.  Unfortunately ours was cursed long ago.  Any who touched it would be turned to darkness.  It’s been hidden away for centuries.  It seems as though some distant cousin of mine has taken it into his head to try to find it.”<br>
<br>
Ayslyn looked back and forth between his two friends.  “Ummm,” he began, “What’s a Moonblade?”  The two other elves stared at him in shock.  Ayslyn looked behind him, trying to figure out what they were staring at.  “What?  What’s with the staring?”<br>
<br>
Alec cleared his throat.  “You’ve never heard of the Moonblades?  They’re famous Silver Elf artifacts.”<br>
<br>
Ayslyn raised an eyebrow.  “Ah, hello…  I’m a Wood Elf.  How in the nine hells would I know about them?  My Silver Elf history is a little rusty.”<br>
<br>
Terrellion sighed.  “The Moonblades are powerful enchanted swords that are given to the noble families of my people.  Each of them had different abilities.  The records of what ours was capable of are lost.  With the Moonblade effectively lost to us, no one felt it necessary to keep track of what it could do.  Only a member of the family who owned it can even touch them.  It is death for any others.  Anyway, I need to go to Evermeet and try to stop him.”<br>
<br>
Ayslyn bounced up from his seat.  “We’ll go with you.  We can help.”<br>
<br>
Terrellion looked dubiously at Ayslyn for a few moments.  “You might not be well received there.”<br>
<br>
Ayslyn grinned.  “I’m not all that well received here either.  I’ll deal.”<br>
<br>
Terrellion smiled.  “Thank you my friend.  I will be glad to have you both at my side.”<br>
