<br>
Alec made his was over to his friend, and handed him a tinder lit from the fireplace.  Ayslyn smiled at him and slowly lit his pipe, taking a few experimental puffs from it.  “Copper for your thoughts Ays?” Alec offered.<br>
<br>
“You’d be drastically overpaying,” Ayslyn quipped back.  He sighed softly as he pushed the window open slightly to let the smoke out.  “It’s nothing really.  I guess that I am just feeling out of sorts.”<br>
<br>
Alec nodded, understanding.  “As soon as Terr’s family gives him all the details, we will get out of here.”  He grinned and continued, “Then you can get back to being a good little savage.”  <br>
<br>
He danced out of the way as Ayslyn punched him lightly.  “Get lost ya scrawny bookworm,” he retorted with a wink.  Alec laughed.  <br>
<br>
The double doors leading into the sitting room flew open and Terrellion strode in to join them.  He grinned and held up a scroll tube.  “We’ve got it.”<br>
<br>
Ayslyn and Alec looked at each other and grinned along with him.<br>
<br>
“Well then,” Ayslyn said as he rose and tapped his pipe out into the fire.  “What are we waiting for?  Lets go get ourselves a cursed sword.”<br>
