<br>
Ayslyn took one of them and pondered it.  A young woman stared back at him from the paper.  Something about it tugged insistently at his memory, but he couldn’t place it.  He was about to put it back down when a voice behind him demanded, “Where the hell did you get that?”<br>
<br>
Ayslyn turned round, surprised, and looked up at Nerram.  “What are you doing here?” he asked.<br>
<br>
“Answer my question.  How did you get a picture of Rose?”<br>
<br>
Ayslyn snapped his fingers as it came to him.  He looked closely at the sketch.  There it was, the rose tattoo peeking up over the low neck of her bodice.  His head whipped about as he stared at Nerram in shock.  “Ummm…  This is a sketch of someone seen with one of Terr’s cousins.  Are you sure it’s her?”<br>
<br>
Nerram looked at Ayslyn with contempt.  “You think that I would forget her?”<br>
<br>
“Well then, how the hell is she still around, and looking pretty young at that?”<br>
<br>
“How am I supposed to know?  But THAT is Rose!”  Nerram was practically frothing at the mouth now.  <br>
<br>
“All right, all right.  It’s Rose.  Relax.”  Ayslyn nodded slightly at Alec.<br>
<br>
“Don’t tell me to relax!  That woman ruin,” Nerram began.  Looking at Alec, his eyes rolled up slowly and he dropped to the ground, fast asleep.  <br>
<br>
Alec grinned and brushed sand from his hands.  “Love that spell.”  Ayslyn chuckled back and nodded.  Entrusting the fighter to the innkeeper, they set out for the resting place for the moonblade.<br>
